Reasoning: The paper discusses the use of recurrent neural networks and sequence-to-sequence networks for multivariate multistep forecasting and reconstruction of ocean wave data. This involves optimization algorithms, feature selection, and error metrics, which are all relevant to machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with oceanography and signal processing, which could fall under cs.OH (Other Computer Science) or cs.SI (Signal and Image Processing).
